Gleason Corp's subsidiary,Gleason Power Systems, said its Torsen torque-sensingdifferential will be supplied as standard equipment in the newAudi 90 Quattro four-wheel drive vehicle.    Initial Torsen differential production for the new Audi 90will not affect earnings in 1987, Gleason said.    The Audi Quattros 80 and 90 models will be introduced inthe U.S. in late 1987, the company said. Reuter&#3;